configuring the git: 
git config —global user.name “” git config —global user.email “” git config —list

git clone (HTTPS Link of the repository)
git status

two step process to add file to github: first: git add (file name)      —> git add . (to add all files of a folder) git commit -m “some message”  publish local change to remote(github) git push origin main


Init command git init
git remote add origin (link)
git remote -v  {to verify}
git branch  {to check the branch}
git branch -M main
git push origin main   or  git push -u origin main {if working on same project for long} {then for next time simply use git push}


Branches
git branch
git branch -M main {to rename branch}
git checkout (branch name)  {to navigate}
git checkout -b (new branch name) {to create new branch}
git checkout -b (branch name) {to delete branch} git push origin (branch name)
 
Merging code
git diff (branch name)  {to compare two branches}
git merge (branch name) or 
create a PR(pull request)



Pull git pull origin main



Undoing changes
case 1:(stage changes) {changes that are added but not commit}
git reset (file name) git reset {to reset changes in all files}

case 2:(committed changes for one commit)
git reset HEAD~1
git log {to check all your commits}

case 3:(committed changes for multiple commits)
git reset (commit hash)
git reset —hard (commit hash) {to undo changes in your editor}



Fork {rough copy of your original project}
 
